    </main>
        <h2>The form tag has an "action" attribute. What does it do?</h2>
        <p>To specify the URL where the form data is sent after submission.</p>
        <h2>The form tag has a "method" attribute. What does it do?</h2>
        <p>To define how the data of form is sent.</p>
        <h2>What is the difference between a "POST" and a "GET"?</h2>
        <p>GET used for data in the URL, visible, limit length,
             and suitable for data query.
             POST used for data save in the request, more secure,
              transmit big data, and suitable for data edit.
        </p>
